news.article_text:

Several analysts responded by downgrading the company, which shifted the market’s focus to competitive pressures and cost challenges.

news.headline: PDD Stock Slides After Temu Parent Posts Mixed Q3 Results
news.summary: Temu parent company PDD Holdings posted third-quarter revenue slightly below estimates, as the Chinese e-commerce company said it is facing stepped up competition.  U.S.-listed PDD stock slid despite posting earnings that beat Wall Street forecast.  PDD said in a news release early Tuesday that it earned an adjusted 21.08 yuan per American depositary share for the September-ended quarter, up 13.4% from a year earlier.

news.headline: PDD Holdings Stock Falls After Mixed Q3 -- EPS Beats but Revenue Misses
news.summary: PDD Holdings (NASDAQ:PDD), owner of Temu, slid nearly 1.5% on Wednesday. The company reported net income of $4.4 billion, up 13% from $3.9 billion. Management warned that consumer spending remains soft.
news.article_text:
This article first appeared on GuruFocus.

PDD Holdings (NASDAQ:PDD), owner of Temu, slid nearly 1.5% on Wednesday after its third-quarter results beat EPS estimates but fell short on revenue.

news.headline: Bitcoin price rises as Trump may pick new Fed chair before Christmas
news.summary: Bitcoin (BTC-USD) climbed sharply on Tuesday, breaking above $91,000. The move marks one of bitcoin’s strongest daily gains in weeks after a stretch of volatile trading. Global digital-asset market capitalisation rose 3.5% to $3.2
news.article_text:
Bitcoin (BTC-USD) climbed sharply on Tuesday, breaking above $91,000 as expectations grow that president Donald Trump could name a more dovish Federal Reserve chair before the Christmas holidays.

The world’s largest digital asset by market valuation is now trading around $91,300, up 4.3% over the past 24 hours. The move marks one of bitcoin’s (BTC-USD) strongest daily gains in weeks after a stretch of volatile trading.
